  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I give my girlfriend space / stop the feeling of having my soul sucked out for the seconds I'm not with her?",
  "response": "It's important to find a balance in a relationship that allows both partners to feel secure and fulfilled while also respecting each other's need for personal space. Here are some steps you can take to give your girlfriend space while also managing your own feelings:\n\n1. **Communicate Openly:** Talk to your girlfriend about your feelings. Share your need for some space and see how she feels as well. Open communication can foster understanding.\n\n2. **Engage in Hobbies:** Rediscover activities you enjoy or pursue new hobbies. This can help you focus on your own interests and give you a sense of fulfillment outside the relationship.\n\n3. **Spend Time with Friends:** Nurturing friendships can provide support and companionship, helping reduce any feelings of dependency on your girlfriend for emotional fulfillment.\n\n4. **Set Healthy Boundaries:** Discuss and agree upon how much time you\u2019ll spend together versus apart. This can help you both feel more comfortable and respected.\n\n5. **Practice Self-Care:** Engage in activities that promote your mental and physical well-being, such as exercise, meditation, or mindfulness. This can help alleviate feelings of stress or emotional drain.\n\n6. **Reflect on Your Feelings:** Take some time to understand why you feel this way. Are there underlying insecurities or fears? Understanding these emotions can help you address them more effectively.\n\n7. **Limit Contact Gradually:** If being in constant communication feels overwhelming, try reducing the frequency of texts or calls, allowing for more natural breaks in your interaction.\n\n8. **Encourage Her Independence:** Support your girlfriend in pursuing her interests and spending time with her friends. A healthy relationship allows both partners to grow individually.\n\n9. **Monitor Your Emotions:** Recognize that feeling drained may indicate deeper emotional needs. Exploring these feelings with a therapist or counselor can be beneficial.\n\n10. **Trust the Relationship:** Remind yourself that being apart does not diminish the love or connection you have. Trust that both of you can maintain a strong relationship even with some distance.\n\nRemember, it\u2019s natural to want to spend a lot of time with someone you care about, but cultivating independence is key to a healthy relationship.",
